      <td valign="top" align="right">
      <div id="CommentBar_1660" style="display:none;">

      
      <span id="FlagComment_1660">
        <a class="iconLink" href="javascript:ajaxLink('FlagComment_1660', '/akira/flagDiscussionComment.do?topicID=2469&commentID=1660')"><img alt="Warning" class="iconLink" src="/images/iconshock/warning_16.gif" border="0">&nbsp;Report Abuse</a>
      </span>
      


            


      </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

      


      The comparisons to California and other state initiatives are not valid.  Those processes are too controlled by the state governments and don't restrict who can advertise for or against initiatives.  The National Initiative for Democracy does remove those government influences and restrict advertising so powerful money interests are not allowed to influence an election.<br/><br/>If we want to empower our citizens to protect themselves from government abuse, democracy is the only way to do that.  Freedom and democracy are intimately connected.

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


  <tr id="row_2046" onmouseover="showDiv('CommentBar_2046');" onmouseout="hideDiv('CommentBar_2046')" class="IdeaScale_Comment_Normal">
    <td valign="top" style="padding:3px;">

